**Algorithm:**
1. For each element in height array, create maximum left array i.e., what is the maximum left bar for every each element.
2. For each element in height array, create maximum right array i.e., what is the maximum right bar for every each element.
3. Iterate height array for each bar, use below formula to find volume of rain water sitting at each bar:
			 ***Volume at bar : Minimum(Maximum Left of the bar, Maximum Right of the bar) x Height of the bar x Width***

**Note:** 
	1. Width of each bar is 1 as per description.
	2. Minimum of max left and max right is taken as water level is retained by lowest height.


```
class Solution {

    public int trap(int[] height) {

        //base condition
        if(height.length==0)
            return 0;

        int volume = 0;
        int[] maxLeft = new int[height.length];
        int[] maxRight = new int[height.length];

        maxLeft = createMaxLeft(height,maxLeft);
        maxRight = createMaxRight(height,maxRight);

        //calculate volume at each bar using formule : min(maxLeft,maxRight)-height
        for(int i=1;i<height.length-1;i++){
            int barVolume = Math.min(maxLeft[i],maxRight[i])-height[i];
            if(barVolume>0)
                volume += barVolume;
        }

        return volume;
    }

    //Dynamic Programming to calculate left max array
    private int[] createMaxLeft(int[] height, int[] maxLeft){
        maxLeft[0] = 0;
        for(int i=1;i<height.length;i++)
           maxLeft[i] = Math.max(height[i-1],maxLeft[i-1]); 
        return maxLeft;
    }

     //Dynamic Programming to calculate right max array
    private int[] createMaxRight(int[] height, int[] maxRight){
        int n = height.length-1;
        maxRight[n] = 0;
         for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
           maxRight[i] = Math.max(height[i+1],maxRight[i+1]); 
        return maxRight;

    }
}
```

