hi [@Harsh sharma](/Harshsharma12) sorry for late response.

You forgot to consider the highest blocks on the left and right sides when calculating the trapped water. To fix this, keep track of the maximum height on both sides while going through the blocks. When calculating trapped water, subtract the current block's height from the maximum height on the respective side.


```java
class Solution {
    public int trap(int[] height) {
        int ans = 0;
        int left = 0;
        int right = height.length - 1;
        int leftMax = 0;
        int rightMax = 0;

        while (left < right) {
            if (height[left] <= height[right]) {
                if (height[left] > leftMax) {
                    leftMax = height[left];
                } else {
                    ans += leftMax - height[left];
                }
                left++;
            } else {
                if (height[right] > rightMax) {
                    rightMax = height[right];
                } else {
                    ans += rightMax - height[right];
                }
                right--;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}

```

