**[142. Linked List Cycle II](https://leetcode.com/problems/linked-list-cycle-ii/) Solution using Two Pointers Approach:**
Note: Basically copy & paste, to recycle the same function, but instead of returning a boolean value "true" if a cycle exists, we will return the output of a helper function (phase 2) and instead of "false", we return "null" as the problem states "if there is no cycle".
```
const detectCycle = head => {
  let p1 = head;
  let p2 = head;

  while (p2 && p2.next && p2.next.next) {
    p1 = p1.next;
    p2 = p2.next.next;
    if (p1 === p2) {
	  return detectCyclePos(head, p2);
	}
  }
  return null;
};

//phase 2 helper function to determine the actual cycle point (not just where the pointers intersected)
const detectCyclePos = (head, intersection) => {
  let p1 = head;
  let p2 = intersection;
  while (p1 !== p2) {
    p1 = p1.next;
    p2 = p2.next;
  }
  return p1;
};
```

