**Approach:**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/c11c92c9-492c-4860-a7d9-75f3ecf0c34b_1657874001.1176662.jpeg)

* let there be two pointers
* s = slow pointer
	* moves one step at a time
* f = fast pointer
	* moves 2 steps at a time
* now if there is a cycle then s and f will meet
* let them meet at point **A**
* now,
	* distance between head to the start of cycle = x
	* distance between the start of cycle and point where they meet = y
	* distance from the point they meet to the start of cycle = z
	* distance travelled by **s = x+y**
	* distance travelled by **f=x+y+z+y**
	* as f travells twice as much as s do
		* **f=2s**
		* x+2y+z=2(x+y)
		* i.e **x=z**
* so now we run a loop until head and s meet
	* why?
	* as x = z so head and 's' will meet after travelling x 
	* and from the current position of s, if it travells a distance=x=z it will reach the starting point of the cycle


**Code:**

```
class Solution
{
public:
    ListNode *detectCycle(ListNode *head)
    {
        bool cycle = false;
        ListNode *s = head;
        ListNode *f = head;
        while (f->next != NULL && f->next->next != NULL)
        {
