# Proof beats
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/b347d3c8-d1de-4bff-a314-03e29925b235_1673459334.003696.png)

# Approach
- If the **row sizes are not equal**, return **false**.
- Create an array of alphabet size (**26 letters**), initialize it with **0**.
- Now let's go through the characters of both strings. For the characters of **the first string** we make **an increment**, for the characters of **the second string** - **a decrement**.
- If **one string is an anagram of another**, then **the resulting array must consist of zeros only**.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $ O(n) $
- Space complexity: $ O(26) = O(1) $

# Code
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
        if (s.size() != t.size()) { return false; }
        vector<int> v(26, 0);
        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
            v[s[i]-'a']++; v[t[i]-'a']--;
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
            if (v[i] != 0) { return false; }
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

